## The Answer

As I've most scientifically shown above, it happens that "almost infinity" is %%undefined%% no matter how accurately you define the "almost" part of it. All thanks to a very specific nature of our friend %%\infty%%.

What does %%undefined%% means in mathematical context? As we've shown above, it designates the answer that can't be contained to a certain range, i.e. %%\infty - \infty%% might be _anything_ from %%0%%, to %%gazillion%%, to %%\infty%% and more.

So, to transcribe it back into normal people's language:

{.kicker.centered}
"Almost infinitely" means "to some unknown extent".

How cool is that? Now I can make all sorts of bald claims sounding like absolute truths. Like watch this: "my article is almost infinitely correct".
